&lt;Oki Electric Industry Co Ltd> may importcar telephones made by its 100 pct U.S. Subsidiary, &lt;OkiAmerica Inc>, for sale in Japan, an Oki spokesman said.    The firm would like to import the car phones, which aremade according to a system developed jointly by Motorola Inc&lt;MOT> of the U.S. And Oki Electric, the spokesman said.    A final decision will hinge on obtaining approval fromJapan's Post and Telecommunications Ministry and whether or notit is feasible to convert the models to meet Japanesespecifications, he said. REUTER&#3;